caption: Absolutely delicious! The dumpling soup was exceptional, I could drink this broth. The gyoza were perfect. Very glad I came across them

Delicious, hot, fast Chinese delivery. I normally reserve five stars for Gourmet restaurants only but this place needs a bump. I don’t know why so many people give it only one star. we’ve ordered here 3 times and every time it’s been so very good. Plenty of food for two people only $40 with delivery and tip through Seamless. Dishes we like are sesame chicken, hot and sour soup (but be careful it is really spicy), Gyoza (good two out of three times), California rolls, dumpling soup, spring rolls, and edamame. They are <2 miles away from our apartment and it usually takes only 15 minutes to arrive.
Drunken noodles were really tasty, and the veggies and herbs in it were super flavorful and fresh. Fast delivery and a great price!

Ordered drunken noodles with shrimp, Thai basil fried rice and fried shrimp wantons. Everything was delicious. The drunken noodles were excellent, the shrimp huge and cleaned. You can actually taste the flavored fresh shrimp in the wantons. The rice was delicious. First time ordering here and was very impressed. I would do it again.

We wanted sushi delivery in BK. Ako Asian Fusion really hit the spot! Their tempura was SO crunchy and perfect too! (Got shrimp and veggie) They also had 8 rolls for $40 (comes with 2 sides or either miso soup or salad. Or 1 miso soup, 1 salad). As you can see, they don’t pile the rice on. I requested 4 rolls with no rice for keto. The only thing I wouldn’t get again is the eel. There were way too many bones.  We also got their tri color summer rolls those were great!  If you’ve never ordered from them on seamless, you might be able to get 25% off!

We LOVED this sushi. Can’t understand the low reviews. It was very fresh and delicious and even the ginger tasted fresher than other places. We had the spicy tuna and salmon avocado and sweet potato rolls and they were ALL better then our usual neighborhood places. And look at the one layer of rice! Even the rice tasted better. [This pic was taken after we’d had a few pieces]
Pad thai noodles was dry and mango salad watery. Wasted my $31.00
Food is fine, but I ordered chicken katsu and the “katsu” sauce was straight-up barbecue sauce. Not katsu at all.
Food was delicious, and delivery was fast

5 stars on seamless (how???), 2 stars here, 0 stars for me.  Got 3 noodle dishes: drunken noodles were pretty ok, pad see ew was not great, tasted nothing like the real thing and had too little sauce, the Udon noodles tasted just like chicken stock and I couldn't eat them.

I wish I was making this up but I couldn't. We ordered sushi and when the delivery man came, we gave him the $42 cash for our meal. We shortly after realized we'd received the wrong meal. Our proper meal showed up a bit later and it was realized that the original meal we received was from Ako and we'd actually ordered from a different restaurant and the delivery man delivered to the wrong address without a receipt. We called Ako and told them they needed to bring out $42 cash back. The driver told the manager that we'd only given him $2. The manager yelled at us, called us liars and told us that he believed his driver over us and hung up. I'm absolutely dumbfounded. I've never experienced this type of customer service anywhere.

This place is a disaster. They mangled my order over the phone, sending mostly wrong items. I called and they said they would send the missing things but still wanted to charge for them. Then they never sent them anyway. Ridiculous place. Update, they just brought the missing parts of the order, 2 hours later!

Garbage service. I ordered delivery, waited an hour, called them, they said they'd call the driver and never did, I called back, they hung up on me when I asked them about the food. There are too many sushi places in NYC to order from these garbage humans.
